com.foreach.across.modules.entity.bind

Class ListEntityPropertyBinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.bind.ListEntityPropertyBinder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EntityPropertyBinder

    public final class ListEntityPropertyBinder
extends Object
    Represents a property value backed by a Collection that is not a map. The getValue() will always return the current value of the collection. The getItems() returns the collection items wrapped as EntityPropertyBinder in a map structure. The key of the map structure does not matter, it simply provides a unique identification for an item in the collection, without relying on the actual index.

    The EntityPropertyBinder.getSortIndex() or every single item will determine the actual order of the resulting collection.

    By default when enableBinding(boolean) is true, the list of items will be reset as it is expected that binding will replace all the items (eg. all of them are submitted by form). This behaviour can be customized by calling setUpdateItemsOnBinding(boolean) with true.

    Since:
    3.2.0
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
    See Also:
    SingleEntityPropertyBinder, MapEntityPropertyBinder

      • getItems

        public Map<String,EntityPropertyBinder> getItems()
        Get the map of items to bind on. This is the actual target for adding items. Note that entries in this map are not sorted according to the EntityPropertyBinder.getSortIndex(), use getItemList() if you want to iterate over the items in order. The item key is available under EntityPropertyBinder.getItemKey().

        Includes all items, including ones with EntityPropertyBinder.isDeleted() true.

        Returns:
        modifiable map

      • getItemList

        public List<EntityPropertyBinder> getItemList()
        Get an ordered - unmodifiable - list of all the items. These will be sorted according to the value of EntityPropertyBinder.getSortIndex().

        Includes all items, including ones with EntityPropertyBinder.isDeleted() true.

        Returns:
        unmodifiable list of all items in order

      • enableBinding

        public void enableBinding(boolean enabled)
        While binding is enabled, the items collection will not remove any (possibly) deleted items. When explicitly disabling binding, the items will be cleared of any deleted items and will be fully cleared if the property itself is deleted.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true if in binding mode, false if not expecting any more changes

      • isUpdateItemsOnBinding

        public boolean isUpdateItemsOnBinding()
        If set to true, the existing items will always be returned when performing data binding, and every item separately can be removed/modified. If false, then it is expected that all items are passed when data binding (replacing them). This is the default mode.

      • setUpdateItemsOnBinding

        public void setUpdateItemsOnBinding(boolean updateItemsOnBinding)
        If set to true, the existing items will always be returned when performing data binding, and every item separately can be removed/modified. If false, then it is expected that all items are passed when data binding (replacing them). This is the default mode.
